               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Zǝmmāre, Eucharistic hymns (fols. 3ra-64vc)
 II) Mawāśǝʾt,
                     Antiphonary for feasts and funeral service (fols. 66ra-94ra)
 
 Additio
                     1.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- A portion of Mawāśǝʾt dedicated to St Mary (Mawāśǝʾt za-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝnä
                        Māryām), omitted in the main text, has been written at the end of Text II
                           (<locus from="93vc" to="94ra">93vc-94ra</locus>), in hand b. It should be
                        inserted into <locus target="#89va">89va</locus> l.1 before the part
                        beginning with “ʿǝzl”.</note>
                     <note>- The quires are numbered separately for Texts I and II. Quire number 6
                        is skipped (Text I).</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
